Astrea of the Stars 15-Aug-21 04:15 PM
It's... quiet. The first thing you notice as you enter this room is as soon as the door closes here, it goes completely silent. You can't hear so much as a yell from the outside - everything inside stays inside and vice versa. There are intercoms here, though, so you'll still hear daily and important announcements. Alongside the walls here are many pipes and wires - you're not sure what they're used for, but you get the sense that they're important. Breaking them via normal means is impossible - even the thinnest wires feel impossible to cut down. There's also some LEDS on some of the pipes - they always seem to be green, and that's probably a good thing. The main attraction of this room, however, is the huge computer (or at least a huge monitor with amore standard sized mouse and keyboard underneath it) that lies at the end of this room. The screen itself shows some interesting information about this place itself - it shows the oxygen level (or, well, the oxygen status - it just says 'Good'), the amount of electricity the place is using (quite a bit), the weather outside of here (changes every day, though it tends to usually be a bit chilly) - nothing so useful that it would help you find out what exactly is going on here, but it's useful information nevertheless. You cannot make the screen show anything else - it's almost as if it were stuck on an app, and not even ALT + F4 will close it. There's also a little text... thing on the bottom right of the screen - it says 'B.F. Analytics'. Huh.
